        "subtitle": "A synthetic dataset for machine learning-based real-time beam direction predict",
        "description": "Real-time Beamforming Optimization for Next-Gen Wireless Networks\n\nA synthetic dataset for machine learning-based real-time beam direction selection, incorporating user mobility, channel state information, and historical network performance.\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\nThe dataset contains the following key features, collected over simulated time steps:\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nsample_id: Unique identifier for each data sample/time instance.\nuser_loc_hist_x_0: 2D Cartesian coordinates (x, y) representing the user's past N locations. This captures user mobility patterns.\nuser_loc_hist_y_0: Integer indices (0 to num_beams-1) representing the beam direction chosen by the system at past N time steps. This provides contextual information about previous beam choices.\nuser_loc_hist_x_1: [no description]\nuser_loc_hist_y_1: [no description]\nuser_loc_hist_x_2: A scalar value (in dB) indicating the overall signal quality at the user's location. A higher SINR generally means better communication.\nuser_loc_hist_y_2: Simplified representation: A vector of channel gains or strengths associated with each of the M potential beam directions. Higher values indicate stronger signal paths.\nuser_loc_hist_x_3: Simplified representation: A vector of channel gains or strengths associated with each of the M potential beam directions. Higher values indicate stronger signal paths.\nuser_loc_hist_y_3: Simplified representation: A vector of channel gains or strengths associated with each of the M potential beam directions. Higher values indicate stronger signal paths.\nuser_loc_hist_x_4: Simplified representation: A vector of channel gains or strengths associated with each of the M potential beam directions. Higher values indicate stronger signal paths.\nuser_loc_hist_y_4: [no description]\ncsi_beam_0: [no description]\ncsi_beam_1: [no description]\ncsi_beam_2: [no description]\ncsi_beam_3: [no description]\ncsi_beam_4: [no description]\ncsi_beam_5: [no description]\ncsi_beam_6: [no description]\ncsi_beam_7: [no description]\nbeam_hist_0: [no description]\nbeam_hist_1: [no description]\nbeam_hist_2: [no description]\nbeam_hist_3: [no description]\nbeam_hist_4: [no description]\nsinr: [no description]\noptimal_beam_index: [no description]\n",
